postcontent: NIB Robinson Armament M96 Expeditionary rifle.  Box is in very excellent shape.  Long sight radius. Left side non-reciprocating charging handle. The M96 is chambered for .223/5.56 NATO cartridge, and uses AR-15 magazines. The M96 is gas operated, with a fixed gas cylinder and moving piston connected to the operating rod and bolt carrier. Equipped with a gas regulator, which allows fine-tuning for low or high powered cartridgesr. The M96 bolt is a six-lug design somewhat similar to an AR-15 bolt but with larger, stronger lugs. The M96 receiver is stamped stainless steel with a special blackening treatment. The barrel is parkerized chromoly steel and the stocks are molded plastic. Incidentally, the buttstock is the one part of the M96 that is interchangeable with the Stoner 63. The M96 has adjustable military-type sights (rear aperture and front protected post).  A website bighammer dot net has a good review of this rifle which is easy enough to find with a google search.  IraqVeteran8888 has a good Youtube video reviewing and shooting an M96 rifle.General appearance is similar to a Stoner 63 rifle.  It was purchased by myself from an estate sale, and proof of that will be provided to buyer.
